values:
Ok, this is just a quicky.  And it's probably going to be my last entry.

I started the journal so that I could start writing again and so that my friends could keep tabs on me.  AFter all, it's easier to write something out and stick it on one place and give everyone a URL than trying to explain the same thing over and over to different people.  However, this has also become very restrictive for me.  I have things I want to write, but I tell myself to wait til I have computer time.  And then it's usually so late that it's not totally worth my time.  If I go back to journalling I'll just keep it to a regular paper journal.  And if there's something really important I want people to know, I'll just email it to everyone or post it on the message board and say "look here."  And again I'm feeling wary about the amount of time I'm spending in front of the monitor.  Yeah, things are getting behind with the site and all and yes I like to see if people are on, but living in front of a monitor is starting to suck again.  Drain my energy if you will.  

Now I'm not leaving the net all together and I'm not abandoning things.  I just think I'm going to let my live journal go.  When I'm on my computer (typing from the folk's computer right now) I'm going to make sure I have everyone's journal main pages saved so that I can still keep up with everyone who still has an account.  

Besides, this place is a little too public for my liking.  I guess that's a silly thing considering, yeah, it's the internet and there's even someone on the end of this very post monitoring what everyone types.  I have some things on my mind that I don't want to share but want to figure out through writing it down, but it's things that are honestly better to keep to myself. Also, I think there is a little bit of a pressure to actually keep it going.  There just aren't enough earth-shattering things going on every single day to merit writing in a semi-public forum.

As I said, I'm not disappearing from the world, I'm just not going to keep the journal.  ^_^  My email is still open, and anyone in the area who monitors this will have my phone numbers, so you can call me if you need me.

So, I bid thee all good evening.

Scheduling at Target has always been less than organised.  In fact, we haven't had anyone who can really do it right in probably four years.  This, however, takes the cake.

There's a new store opening in the next county and some people were being sent out to the site for what is known as Planorama.  Basically it's setting up all the shelves and price markers and such.  I see on my schedule for the week that I have the 1st through the 3rd open.  Hot Damn!  Three days off!  Thursdays I keep open anyway for appointments and just to garuntee that I actually get a day to rest (I can't take off weekends because that's when the most hours are given.).  I went in just moments ago to check the new schedule for the week from next and I see two of my supervisors, Shelly and Lois, taking a smoking outside.  We all get into a conversation about the fact that my name was on a list that had been up for a week for people who were doing plano at the North Olmstead site.

What...the...fuck...

Just so you know, I have NEVER worked planogram team in the entire time I've worked for Target.  Why on God's green Earth would I work plano team for another freaking store?  Shelly said George was going to put me specifially in their Food Avenue.  Bull shit.  You don't need me for that.  There's nothing special about putting little sicky tags on the shelving and then filling them in with said products.  Why were they pulling from the non-plano team anyway?  Plano works overnight and friggin early shifts and don't work every single day.  Why not just send all of them out there?  Lois commented that someone from the clothing department was sent over without even being asked.  I wasn't asked either, damn it!  Nor did anyone even try to call me the past few days wondering where I was.  They told me not to worry about it because they agreed that it's stupid how things were arranged.    

Now, I do feel idiotic for not reading the paperwork close enough.  That is my malfunction, i admit I should have kept closer eye on things.  Still, why didn't someone come and talk to me about it?  Why didn't they make a note on the schedule grid?  It just blows my mind...

EDITED THREE HOURS LATER
Because this whole ordeal was making me litterally sick to my stomach, I had Mom drive me up to the shop and I talked to Dan about it.  Yeah, my name was on the list, but he said there had been some miscommunications about the whole thing (when one of the higher managers talks from the side of his mouth and says "it's Target" you know it's a big stupidity on the part of corporate) and said it's ok and that I don't have to go in tomorrow and I won't have any corrective action placed against me.

Now I can heave a huge sigh and collape and take a nap.

This one might burn a few brains. Just thought I'd warn you ahead of time. Dave sent me another random bit of fan art he picked up. Nice Japanese fox/wolf boy. There was a copyright on the picture so I figured I'd see if I could find anything else by this particular artist or at least the character. I stuck the artist name in Google and found a link to the Japanese site and had Google do a horrible translation job to make it easier to navigat. (It didn't actually help much.) As it turns out, Soyer the Wolf Boy is one of only two male characters who are also the only normally drawn characters on the site. The rest are his (or her) Busty Animal Girl Unit characters. And when it says busty, that is the understatement of the decade. I mean these poor girls (all of whom are underage on top of that) have tits 100 times bigger than the rest of their bodies. Like this poor sap for instance... What the hell? Seriously! This just confuses me to know end. These girls wouldn't even be able to walk to the bathroom with breast that big! It doesn't end their either. I fished around more, hoping to find some female characters resembeling something normal, and found a girl who not only needs a drastic reduction, but can't stop her milk from running. Hello! It doesn't work that way, not even with the "cow girls." Don't even get me started on the hermaphrodite... Now, as it's in Japanese, and I can't read or speak Japanese, I can't tell if this is all meant to be a parody or if this person is actually serious. Either way, it's very very scary and makes me wonder what on earth these people are smoking. I know Japanese women are generally smaller built, but geeze, the men don't need that much compensation in their fantasies, do they?
Remind me to tell you about the county fair when I'm not quite so tired.

Good grief is Drake wearing me down.  Not only is he writing these unnessisarily long interviews, but he keeps putting out revised versions.  After starting to edit and tweak the first part of his 3rd interview (I have three through ten, ten actually having four parts.  That's right, FOUR!) and I get about half way through, and what does he do?  He goes back and makes another revision.  Now granted, there were a few things in this version I missed, and it's good to go back and check the grammar as many times as needed, but a lot of changes he was making looked like he was taking a perfectly good sentence and putting it through a grammar shreader.  I started taking the most recent version and tweaking it, but it doens't look like there're any major changes, like tons of lines added or anything.  So I'm pretty much going over the same exact work again, making the exact same changes.  And then he comes on messenger the next night (tonight) and asks to pick up our editing meeting were we left off, which was with a version that had not been fully edited yet.  -_-;;  I think he was a little upset or maybe disappointed that I wasn't done yet, but I can't read interviews (or any other written works) as fast as this boy can churn them out.

I have to wonder how Dave put up with it for so long on his own.  I realise that I'm going about things differently:  I'm trying to work with the writers to make their work better while Dave just made the edits and worked with it best he could before posting them directly.  I try not to edit in such a way that it takes  away from the individual style of the submitter, but in Drake's case, I'm ready to make an exception.  I just want to fix it up, finish it, and not let him touch it too much again so that he doens't mess up the grammar any more.  Yet his pieces, for how long they are, somehow manage to be incomplete.  He takes ages to say one thing but then forgets to add a detail that would make things clearer and jumps to the next thought.  

I seriously can't wait til I finish dealing with him so that I can move on to administrative site business and then to my own work.

I wonder how people possibly do this kind of work for a living... @_____@

I think I've mentioned it before, but this is now the offical call.  I've asked Jenna to do a special 5th anniversary pic for the HQ.  I'm starting getting ideas and information together now so that it's not a rushed, last-second project.  What I need from everyone is not only an initial ok to use their character, but also some details for Jenna.  I need information like height, weight, body build and type, eye colour, hair colour and style, "normal" outfits and things like that. If you have pictures already or screen shots that give a general idea, send them to me and I'll send them all along to her.

Here's who I hope will consent:
Ertai, Firiel, and Bowe
Samuel McCloud
Aftershock
Raptor
Grey Wolf
Jason McCloud

She's done pictures of Amy, LN, Jolteon, and Butterfly Girl so she has an idea of what to do with them, though I'll have to send along some height references.  I'd also like to have Pete in there if Dave and Pete can figure out what he looks like.

If you're on the list, let me know ASAP if you'd like to be involved.  I really want to make this special.  The anniversary is Valentine's Day, so let's get the ball at least rolling.

<lj-cut text="It's too long to not link it.">
I havent' exactly been keeping up on my promise to take better care of myself.  I've been trying to get back to HQ work so I've been spending more time in front of the computer again.  As such, I've gotten away from trying harder to prepare my own lunches for work and such.  It's lead to me eating more of the food at work, all of which makes me physically ill. On top of that, I've been working more hours the past few weeks.  It's good for the paycheque, but it has been horrible on my legs, feet, knees, and sleep.  It doesn't help that one of my shoes for work is broken.  Part of the side lining is gone, so my heel is litterally falling off the sole when I walk. Very uncomfortable.  But the other shoe is perfectly fine, and I don't want to have to spend $25 for another pair.  (yeah, I know I can find cheaper sneakers if I look, but I have a hell of a time finding shoes, so if I find something I like, I have to get it.)  

Also, my teeth are giving me a hard time.  Have been for a few months.  I've just been scared to do anything about it because I've been worried about my coverage.  I have dental insurance, but I don't know what my deductable is.  I dont know how much I'll have to shell out of pocket (which will have to go on the credit card, which already has a ballance that's way too high for me) before the insurance actually starts paying for things.  If things are ok and I just need routien checkups for a while and I just have sensitive teeth or something, I'll be ok and might pay $30 office fees or something.  However, if I need work done, I'll be screwed.

All of this combined is not making for a happy girl at all.

Job thing still isn't going very well.  I've heard of another bank that's looking for help, so I guess I could give it another shot.  Still not sure though, especially after the last time.  However, even with pulling closet to 40 hours the past couple of weeks, my paycheques are still just under $400 every two weeks.  That's not nearly enough to cover my bills and try to get the kind of food I actually want to put in my body instead of just setteling for whatever my parents buy.  (Doesn't help that I seem to be running out of work clothes.  Most of my shirts have rips and tears in them or are getting old and worn or something like that.  I swear I'm too hard on my stuff.)

My money situation has made me ponder a job that I've never considered before: serving.  I've always said that I could never work for such a horribly low wadge (for you in the UK, miminum wadger for waitresses is under $3 an hour), espeically when the work is so demanding.  I also figured I could never keep all the orders straight and be able to keep up an appearance where I don't look like a rag doll and manage to deal with people all night.  Still, if you get hired at the right place, I hear you can make a couple hundred a night just in tips, though I know that such pay is irratic.  One night the place can be exceedingly busy and you're getting money left and right, the next night could be completely dead and you get nothing or all the tips are put on credit card, which means you don't see them until offical pay day. However, I also know that it's going to be rare to find a job at another retail or restaurant venu where I'll make anything close to $8 an hour.  I mean, I won't be making $8 an hour at Target until the first of November.  That's still two and a half months away, and it's taken me five years to build up to that without taking any of the bitch managment jobs.  I know I've been there long enough that I could be in a position of authority, and I've been offered spots before, but I've seen how my store operates and find that it's not worth getting myself stressed out.  I hear of many team leads that are sick of their jobs and either want out of their departments or positions or out of the company all together. 

(The company is spreading itself thin again.  They're putting a store up in North Olmstead, which will take business away from the Rocky River store, which is one of the branches that took away from my store.  yet we're all expected to make thousands in sales every day and stay within payroll and make sure the stores look and operate perfect.)  

I guess I just want to keep my options open.  There aren't a whole heck of a lot of opertunities in this area for someone like me.  At the moment, my main goal is to earn enough to take care of my affairs here so that I can move to England and start my new life with David.  Yeah, when I get there I'll probably end up in the same kind of work, but at least UK servers make normal minimum wadge as well as tips.  Annie commented that I'll be tired as hell working all these hours at these different places (I'm going for at least 20 hours some place during the day and then whatever I can squeeze out of Target) but I look at Dave and see him working more than 20-hour shifts and know that I have to be able to keep up.  I'm not going to let him do all the work alone to support me, and I don't want him litterally working himself to death like my father's done his whole life.  (Plus there's that little scary detail of nervous breakdowns running in the family because they all have demanding and stressful jobs...)

I'm wondering if I'm to the point where, if I had the mainstream idea perfect body, I'd just go and be a stripper and get it over with.  Yeah, I know half of you would beat me for it then drag me out of the place and set it on fire.  I'm not that crazy about such an idea myself, but there are times here and there I wonder.

By the way, anyone thinking about seeing The Dukes of Hazzards should wait until it's available for under $5 at a smaller cinema or wait for the rental release.  Don't waste $8.25 like I did.  (That was just the ticket price.  I didn't get any snacks.)  The best parts where the actually stunt driving and the outtakes durning the credits.  The rest of the movie, while mildely entertaining, was mostly the stupid kind of funny.  Oh, and the only females in the movie who were not out-right sluts were Linda Carter (aka Wonder Woman from the 70s) and the lady cop who told Daisy to go screw herself when she tried to lure at least a dozen cops from a road block and then yelled at them for being a bunch of idiots because the were going to up and leave their posts for the sake of some slut.  Oh, and Jessica Simpson can't act for shit, and she looks horrible in that tan and all the makeup.  And the guy who played Beau has really bright expressive eyes.  I think that was about it.  The entire time I was praying that people like this are not allowed to reproduce because they're either total morons or just straight crazy. It's a good movie if you feel the mood for something that's less than intelectual, as it screams "guy movie."  

My brother is worrying me again with this additude that everyone that is his idea is a bad guy should be tortured and killed.  I mean, he was scoaling the Ninja Turtles for crying out loud!  Mom found him a special Christmas episode of the recent series.  Michelangelo is out wondering around and finds a group of thugs are hijacking a truck of toys meant for charity and is going to pawn them on eBay for big bucks, so of coure there's the usual fight scene and subsequent car chase.  Now, Mickey is jumping all over the place trying to avoid getting shot.  Alex argues that he should do like Frank Castle (Alex is on a Punisher kick, which scares the shit out of me) and grab the other gang member and use him as a human shield so that he doens't take damage and so that particular thug dies quickly with little effort on Mickey's part.  Now, you'd think that after being a fan for how many years, Alex shoudl realize that such behaviour is not only inappropriate for a children's cartoon in the United States, but is not the Ninja Turtle's style.  They're not into gut spilling.  I also pointed out that Mickey had a kitten in his jacket at the time, as he had decided to adopt it, and that he had to be more careful with how he fought so that the kitten didn't get hurt.  Alex's explination was that it's the writers fault for that: they should have never gotten the kitten involved and should have given Mickey a free shot to break all their necks in one shot.

Now, I know that my brother is autisitc, so he's not going to reason in the same way a "typical" person does.  I also know that school was absolute hell for him because of his stutter.  At the same time, he's decided to hole himself with his games (which he cheats at to win) and cartoons and doen'st want to really go outside.  In high school I tried to take him to drama club meetings with me, and my friends liked him (hell, one girl though he was cute).  But no, Alex decided that those kinds of people are too crazy for him and that he wasn't going to do all that work building sets outside school if there was no pay involved. -_-  

I don't know what to do with him anymore.  Dispite what he believes, Dad can't make Alex "normal" or "a man" by trying to treat him like a normal kid.  It's not going to work.  Alex is never going to be typical.    He makes no effort to do anything but cheat at his games, thinking that it's somehow serving the purpose of virtual justice since he's not strong enough to be a vigilante.  I'm about ready to uninstall his Punisher game, hide the disks as well as the Punisher movie, and steal his Action Replay cheat system.  I've worked on and off trying to find some kind of group or club where he'd be around more adults like him, but it's hard working around all the different schedules to actually drive him anywhere. 

Maybe I'll just go to bed soon.  Can't do much about it all tonigh. </lj-cut>

Had a brief talk with Dave about Wolf.  I didn't go into great detail about what Taylor and Heather and I have talked about in reguards to him, but he says to just leave stuff to them for the moment.  So maybe Dave has a better handle on things than I thought.  Anyway, he also knows now that Heather knows CSS, so I certainly hope he'll ask her for help in the future.  

In the mean time, I've gone back to working on site submissions.  I'm focusing on Drake again just because his pieces are so long.  I'll have to check back with what needs looked over on the site and try to pass out reviewing duties.  However, it seems a lot of people are going to be going back to school or have started working or something like that, so I don't know who can do much.  Since I'm not going to have Heather worry about recoding the site for the moment, I might have a day where we bring one of Dad's computers into the living room and we can work on submissions together.  She reads faster and has better grammar than I so it would work better that way.

I've commissioned Jenna for an anniversary project for the site.  Feb 14th will be the HQ's 5th year in operation.  There wasn't much done for the 4th anniversary, so I was hoping to go for something special this year.  Basically it's going to be a big group shot of the older members who are in Dave's group of friends.  Characters included so far: J, LN, Amy C, Pete (if I Dave and Pete have an idea of what he looks like), Ertai, Firiel, Bowe, Aftershock, Sam McCloud, Jason McCloud, Grey Wolf, Raptor. I think I've covered everyone relavent.  Yeah, there are tons of people on the site, but these are special ones.  When Dom the MacArthurs come back from their vacations, I'm gonna get stat details for the characters to pass on to her.  I know that February is a ways away, but better to start getting ideas now so that it's not a rushed last-second picture.

Hours at Target are picking up, probably a combination of the back to school rush and the fact that a lot of people will be either going on leave or taking reduced hours to go back to classes.  I've been getting hours in the 30's range the past few weeks and picking up little shifts here and there as alotted.  I'm hoping I'll be able to put a little more aside over the next few weeks and getting a little closer to getting the bills up to date.

Just a quicky.  I probalby won't use it much, but I finally installed AIM because there are certain individuals I needed to speak to who are not on MSN.  Like I know I need Christina and Chris' IM names.  Email me by my MSN account address if you want to put me on your buddy list.

Got a letter from the bank.  Didn't get the job.  Have to go out on the rounds again.

On a lighter note, I finally got HP 6 and Liam's package came today.  *gives him massive amounts of hugs*

A little bit of sleep shouldn't be too much to ask.  Seriously.  The kindergarten crowd has NO idea just how lucky it is to have even the opertunity for rest/nap time.  I would love to have two hours or so to just be able to sleep off all the stress from the morning or the pervious night.  These days of being up late and then having to be up at the ass crack of dawn and then being required to stay up later again that evening is getting on my nerves.  

It doesn't help that I'm a horribly picky sleeper.  I'm not like my boyfriend who can crash anywhere and everywhere to catch a quick nap.  I need a place that's dark, quiet, and cool.  I need to be reclined and covered, and I need to find a comfortable position, and more than ever I've needed the bear from Dave.  It's sad that I've gotten to the point where I don't sleep well without it.  

I can't get that at my house.  My brother is up from about 7 to midnight in the house, mere feet from my bed, and he'll have the computer going to look up something on GameFAQ, be playing some DVD or another either on the compy or on the normal player, and he'll be playing the video game with no sound.  I can't sleep like that!  I need a lack of activity so that my body doesn't keep itself awake out of needed to know what the hell is going on.  Does't help that I'm also forced awake by the morning sunlight coming through the windows.  Right now we only have mini blinds on the windows and no normal curtains, so I can't block it and keep the room dark.  (I seriously need those heavy duty curtains you find in hotels.)  I can't even wake up just to use the toilet and then go back to sleep.  I'm not alert but I'm still awake then.  And it can take me up the three hours some nights to actually calm myself down enough to actually fall asleep.

I need Horlicks.  I brought some back last from my last trip to England and it actually helped a little.  Most of you UK people have my address.  If you ever want to do something nice for me, send me some Horlicks, specifically the chocolate kind with the little sleeping monkey on the jar.  I need that far more than Galaxy right now.

This is also one of the reasons I wanted to work in some kind of office setting.  I want a normal, regularly set work schedule where I know every day I have to be up by this time and I'll be home by this time.  With the flexible schedule, I never know what I'm going to be doing from day to day, and it really messes me up.  One day I don't have to be up at all, the next I'm doing a full time closing where I finish around 930 or 10 and get home 5 or 10 minutes later then take hours to get to sleep, then have to be up around 530 to get ready for a 730 starting time, which always makes me feel sick because I can't eat that early without feeling the need to throw up.  It doesn't last either; I'm hungry again by 9 and might not get a break until 10 or even 1130, and then I don't have much to choose from.  It's really wearing down on me.  

I wouldn't even be typing this now if I didn't have to be awake to drive down to freaking Cleveland to get my car to the mechanic.  I would be in bed, extra pillow over my head, trying to get some resemblance of sleep, then feel guilty for staying in bed for an extra two or three hours without actually falling asleep.  Stupid vicious cycles.

Maybe I can just get tranquilizers.  I need something that's going to quickly knock me out and let me sleep (deeply) for at least 9 hours straight without interruption.  Heather won't let me get on sleeping pills because we know at least one person who was physcially addicted.  If I still talked to George with any frequency, I'd ask if he knows of any tribal remidies.  This is just getting rediculous.

First of all, I'm feeling much better today. Second, I'm slowly making my way through my projects. One gift afgahn is finished and put aside for when I see this person. Another I was going to add to but decided it was fine the way it was. (Didn't darn well feel like dealing with it either.) I dug through the piles of boxes in the various storage areas and found the box with my felt plushy pattern that I started working on...at least last summer. Aftershock may want to take extra caution when clicking the link. Ph34r Teh R4ppy! Doesn't look quite as I had hoped, but still cute. ^_^ Next will be to tackle the dress that's been sitting in pieces in a plastic bag for the past two or three years. :p

God I suck.  Seriously, I suck.  The past few months I can't be arsed to do anything.  Getting out of bed has almost become a chore.  I only do it because I don't like holding my water so long.  I'm running on auto pilot 24/7 and I can't find the motivation to do much of anything.  I'm always feeling sick, and now that I'm even more aware of the kinds of things I'm putting in my system, it makes sense that everything I eat makes me feel sick.  At the same time, I don't have the money to pay for the things that would make me healthier.  I haven't been able to honestly write in ages.  I can't even open my unfinished files without feeling ill at how horrible they are or at how little "inspiration" I have.  My brain and even my soul (yes, finally stepped over the line into Drama Queen Land...) feel like they're rotting.  I'm slower than ever, and I just can't get anything done.  I have a job that drives me nuts, yet I have no real way of escaping.  I have no money to put towards my future.  Every other day I want to go for the pain killers and swallow and entire bottle.  Whenever I talk to people, it's always about depressing things and about how I'm so terrible and how I hate myself, and I'm sure everyone is getting really, really pissed off at me for it.

Maybe I just need to go to bed...

Fantastic Four.  Pretty good movie, not sure how far it deviates from the original story line.  Why they tried to make Sue into a slut is beyond me.  She always had her blouse undone, she had WAY too much makeup on the entire time, and kept stripping down.  And Jessica Biel (or however you spell it) looks like crap as a blonde.

Not much else today.  Got up before the ass crack of dawn for a short shift where I again didn't do all I could because I just didn't freaking care, came home and put in a web application for one of the banks for a teller position.  I hope I get that one.  I know I'd still have to deal with the public, but at least it't potentially days with 20 hours a week and more holidays off than you can shake a stick at.

Your matches, in order, are as follows: 1: Sylphiel Nels Rada 2: Xelloss 3: Zelgadiss Graywords 4: Filia ul Copt 5: Zangulus And the second one really scares me. For the test, go here. http://www.inverse.org/tests/slayers/index.cgi For those of you not familar with Slayers, go here. http://www.inverse.org/ So, who would you be?

Checking the message board just depresses me more than ever.  It's not the general conversation or even the stupid spam forum.  It's the Contributor's form.  It's become so disorganized.  I tried to set it up in such a way that it would help us to better sift through all the submissions, but they're coming in faster than we can deal with, and we don't have a system down pat for actually saying who reviews what and things like that.  It just reminds me of how much we've gotten behind.  

At least Wolf's managed to get a few coding things sorted.  I know there are more issues to be delt with, but it's a start.  Though I'm still a little confused as to this comic updating process.  The directions Wolf gives on the main page seem a little cryptic.  If I could figure it out, I'd start getting Phil's Tails' Revenge comics posted.  Come to think of it, I may be missing an issue.  I'll have to talk to him about that when he's on next.

There's just too few hours in a day and I'm too slow to work those few hours.  I want desperatly to get all the site work finished and updated, but I know I have a boat load of my own issues to deal with in my daily life and changes I have to start making.  On top of that I've been hit with an idea for an art project, but I have to finish the one I'm working on now, which has been in the making for at least a year working on and off.  Just too much to finish...How the hell did David manage it on his own for so long?

Maybe I should invest in Nyquil...  Silly of me to think that I could actually get back to some kind of decent sleep pattern after the boys left.  I've been in a daze the past few nights just because I can't get to sleep.  Though it doesn't help that Target had me working the 7:30 shift my first day back and that in the evening Annie, Megan and I had a hell of a time getting out of Avon Commons after the fireworks.  Why didn't they have the police out there directing traffic sooner and why didn't they have the trafic lights on normal routien instead of the late-night flashing pattern?  Honest to God, there was more than one accident waiting to happen in that lot, and we were almost one of them.  Stupid assholes trying to jump out from their parking spaces trying to make new lanes thinking they'll get out sooner.  Idiots...

Getting back to work was...well, depressing.  It happens pretty much every time I go back to Target after a long time away.  And it tends to get worse.  I was pretty much a zombie the entire time, and I didn't get nearly as much work done as I could have because I just didn't feel like it.  Another guilt trip for myself, especially since I'm the only one with experience on duty for the next few weeks.  Why does my supervisor go  on so freaking many vacations?  About a month and a half before I took my time off, she had a week and a half away.  Then she had about the same amount of time while I was gone, then I come back and she has yet ANOTHER week and a half off, as well as days here and there throughout the month.  I have never seen anyone take so much vacation time in my life!  The other team leads at her level don't take nearly so much time off.  How much time has she been saving up?  Geeze.  She's hardly been here all summer.

I guess I shouldn't let it get to me too much.  I know that I'll never be satisfied with what goes on at that branch.  I've been there nearly five years, I know how things go.  Pretty much all of us are just trying to hang on to our sanity just a little bit longer until something better comes along or because this is the best deal to be found.  I've stayed as long as I have because I take classes on and off and I need a place that's good with changing my scheduleing every few months or so.  

I'm hopeing that there are some openings at the local banks for tellers.  I wouldn't want to be a loan officer though.  I don't want to push mortages.  They're a pain in the ass as they are and I really don't understand them.  Just let me do the cashier work and I'll be fine.  I'm not fond of the idea of doing bank work (maybe out of worry that I'll screw up someone's account beyond repair) but the majority of openings around here seem to be retail and fast food and I'm getting sick of that quickly.  I'd get more holidays off and I'd have shorter work hours and could still take maybe a night class here and there.  I really miss that.

I'll have to get things sorted tomorrow.

Another thing I've learned over the last 24 hours: Clay Akins sucks.  Seriously, he has a really flat voice, nothing exciting about it at all.  Megan played one of his CDs while we were trying to survive the traffic out of the Commons last night, and I wanted to break the disk.  This is the kind of thing that American Idol promotes as singing?  Grow up, people.  I'd rather listen to opera that his kind of shyte.    Opera singers train classically for years before getting into professional performing and are way more interesting to listen to.

This is an odd sensation.  I actually have my computer at my disposal again.  I'm online while on my own computer with my keyboard, my lovely old keyboard with the writing wearing off the keys from overuse, talking to people again and still at an ungodly hour.

I intend to give as full a report on the vacation as I can later, but right now my brain is feeling airline fried, so I'll leave it at this tonight.

I miss him so much...

As is customary before one of Dave's visits, we've been frantically cleaning and recleaning and rearranging the house today.  Things look pretty cozy in the living room right now.  I wish they could stay that way really. But everything will be either put back in the garage or shoved in a random room for storage when he's gone.  There's still lots of work to do on the house itself, lots of walls to tear down and put back up and such.  Still, a lot has been accomplished on the house and I hope that the trend will continue until this house is finally finished once and for all.

I'm nervous about him arriving tomorrow of course.  I want things to go well and i want Ben and he to enjoy themselves.  Though my worries are mainly with the schedule I put together for them that it still under revision.  One day has to be changed around because my grandmother is sick and she can't take us into Cleveland so we'll just visit briefly, though I don't know what time, and I still don't know what time we'll all go to D&Bs Saturday evening.  

I also don't know how things are going to go with the Hunters.  I don't even know Zach's little brother's name!  It's it funny that the site-member visit that I am the least comfortable with is the one that my parents are having the least difficulty accepting.  Then again, it's not me phycially going anywhere, so I guess they figure it's safer for me this way.  Honestly, I have no idea what to say to them.  I haven't even called them yet.  And I have no idea what we'll talk about.  I haven't really spoken much with Zach the past few months because we've both been working.  Normally we end up just bitching to one another or we're trying to pull one another out of a funk.  I don't want to have to deal with that now.  In truth, I don't think we've known Zach long enough to really warrent a visit, but I have a hard time letting him down because it's been such a challenge to get him to stay positive.  He's really a good boy and we were all so worried about him before and I don't want to chance ruining all the progress.

The more I think about it, I'm also terrified of meeting the MacArthurs.  I havne't talked to Mary in a year at least because she's never on messenger.  When I talk to Phil, I try to be big sisterly but I just come out sounding like an ass.  Rob's a sweetie like Phil but he's so much more intelligent than I that it's really intimidating.  He's from a family of liberal arts teachers and is a philosophy major, and just the way he writes blows me away.  It's not often that I get to speak to him either, and the last few times he's been in a group chat, he confuses me with his depates and academic talk.  He doens't make me fell retarded on purpose, it's just the way I feel around someone who knows so many five-sylable words and uses them regularly and then goes off on tangets about various "isms" pertaining to schools of throught that I've never heard of and therefore know nothing about.  It's very frustrating.  I should count myself lucky to know someone like that, but I always end up feeling horrible because I can't keep up.  No, not everyone is going to be a genious, but I really hate being one of the "average" people in this respect.  Just reminds me of how far behind I am with little to no hope of catching up.

I guess I'll just deal with that issues in due time.  There's not much I can do and these are my friends.  They wouldn't agree to this sort of thing if they didn't like me.

It's going to be strange actually being around Dave again.  I fear I become too acustomed to not seeing him.  I love him dearly and I don't want to lose him, but there are times when I wonder if we're drifting apart.  Since February I've hardly seen or heard from him.  When I do have some time with him, either I don't know what to say or we end up doing cutsey flirting stuff.  I don't mind that at all, but I miss the times before we visited when we could spend hours upon hours on the phone talking about everything and anything.  I know not every couple gets to spend lots of time together (my sister and her man live together but never see one another) but it makes me uneasy for some reason.  I get caught up in RPing with Zach and Greg (even more so with Greg) and when Dave falls asleep at the keyboard I find myself spilling my guts to Taylor if something's on my mind.  I'd rather be able to spill to David and be able to recieve his affection at the same time.  I want affection that I can't get from the other boys.  

I guess I'll just have to see how things are when he's here.  It's different trying to get used to him being around again.  I'll be happy to see him though.  I've missed him so much.  It's like having a part of me taken away when I leave him...

Stupid Atlantic ocean...

I've hard David isn't doo well.  At all... This is what I've been told.  I can't be sure of what's going on with him.  He's worked himself too hard apparently...and I can't do anything at the moment to check on him.     I really have no idea what to do now.  At this second, I guess all I can do is just talk to people and keep busy cleaning the house in hopes that he can still come. 

God is sucks not being there for him.  I have no idea how he's doing.  I miss him as it is, but knowing this just makes it all the worse...if that's a word.  >.<

So I told Dad about the pictures of the Ertai clan.  I asked him if he wanted to see them tonight since he was the one that requested them.  He said something about putting them somewhere where he had access so that if anything happened to me he'd know who to come looking for.  I'm not quite sure if that's a yes or a no on if I can go to be honest.  I'm afraid now that if I so much as stub my toe Dad will freak.

I should be more thankful.  My father has worked himself to near death to provide for me and he sacrificed a lot for my sake and continues to do so.  I also know that a lot of parents just have no reguard for their children and I'm glad Dad isn't one of them.  Still, I feel every day like I would be happier with another family.  It's horrible and selfish of me to think this, I know, but it feels like I'm always at odds with Dad, like I can never be exactly what he wants from me.  I'm not even totally sure what that is.  I know he wants me to "stop playing around" and get a "real degree" and a "real job" so that I can support myself, but every career test I've taken points to the liberal arts, which isn't exactly a booming field (unless you count reality show development and production).  He hammers it into my head that my time in theatre class was a waste because I'll never sleep with anyone for a job (does he really think so little of me that he thinks I'm going to get into porn?) and that I need to buckel down and get to work.  I know he's trying to be tough love, and I know I have my head in the clouds too much, but I don't think he really has any faith in me.  Or he'd be happier with me if I were out of the house.  I'd love to be out on my own, believe me, but that's not going to happen right now.  It's expensive out there.  If I could get another job and Annie got a better deal at work and Alex got another job, we might be able to possilbly get something, but then I'd have no savings to move to the UK.

~*~*~*~

Another differnect: Privacy.  I just had to wait 5 min for my mom to go away before I could start writing again.  If she knew I had a public journal, she's be all worried about someone hacking into the account and either stalking me or stealing my identity.

I feel ready to vomit.  I'm starting to wonder if I'll ever be able to have a normal sleep cycle ever again. 

I was up til almost 3am because of a certain furry boy last night.  I guess it wasn't as bad as it could have been but I might still put him in a head lock next time I see him and give him the Dutch rub of his life, just on princple.  

The talk was supposed to make me feel better, but really it made me feel even worse. As usual, I'm the bad guy.  I'm the one being a raving bitch while the person that irritates me is the living saint.  There's never been anything wrong with Nicky...it's all been me.  Just like with Cyber I was just upset that the community looked up to her instead of to me.  It's really quite pathetic that I need validation from total strangers when I know I have people who already love me no matter what.  Stupid want of power trips...

I added a new global moderator to the boad last night.  Wolf requested that he at least be able to pin topics and that was the best way to really go for it.  Besides, he's site staff now.  Seems logical to have him as board staff.  Though I think there are far too many people on board staff.  I mean, we have, what, five admins now?  There's Dave because it's his site, Cyber and Lightning as technical admins, Taylor takes care of member business. Then we have the abuse-of-power accounts that are Cy's Testing Dummy and Amy.  I really think Dave is the only one entitled to such an account, but that's just me.  I don't know wny Cyber has one as well.  And then there's me.  I don't really do much.  I try to get some kind of organisation to the submissions and try to organize things that way, but I really don't do much else for board or site operations. Yeah, I rearranged the forums once, but that's kids stuff.  I haven't programmed skins (though neither has Cyber) and I'm not active daily in actually participating with topics.  It's taken me a year and three months to get over the 200-post mark.  

I've been thinking about stepping down again.  Maybe being kept either as a global mod or as the mod for the Staff Lounge or something so that I can still have access to the Bank.  It was my idea, so I don't want to be cut off from it.  Plus I think I have the passwords to the Amy account.  If it really comes down that I need to do something that falls under admin duties, I can just log in there.  I mean seriously, what do I do there besides start trouble?  Every time I open my big fat mouth, something goes wrong: someone gets their feelings hurt or is offended and a fight starts and everyone gets upset and then Taylor usually has to sort things out.  I hate being a burden on him just as much as I hate causing trouble for David.  Hell, the main reason I stay with the site at all these days is for David's sake.  He's threatened to shut down the entire operation if I ever quit, and he'll do it.  He doens't make idle promises.  And we've kept the site together for almost five years.  I don't want things to die after all the work we've all put into it and especially when the merger has just begun to FINALLY progress.

Stupid decisions...

I'm wondering if this should be my last year for CDC camp too.  I really don't do that much good at camp, not like the outstanding progress I had with my first charge.  Plus I'm always going away to Europe around that time, so why bother confusing a child by not always being there?  This will be, what, four years now?  Maybe five?  I've put in my time.  No use wasteing the time of others.  Besides, I'm really the last person who should be handleing children, even for just a few hours once a week.  They'll more than likely catch some strange vibe from me and end up having more problems than they began with.

~*~*~*~

More differences between a computer journal and a paper one: the noise.  I really don't like the buzzing of computers.  Not when I'm trying to have a quiet, contimplative moment.  It ruins the atmosphear.  The clicking of keyboard keys does't help either.  Especially since I do tend to be a loud typer.  I'm harder on my keyboards than I should be. (I've been told I type as though I were using one of the old fashioned typwriters where you did litterally have to hit the keys to move the piece to make the impression.)  I like to write in the quiet.  My best time to write seems to be at night where there's nothing awake to disturb me.  And I like writing by candle light if I can.  There's something about it that seem more, I don't know, romantic maybe.  It's probably not good for my eyes, but I can write for hours by candle or lamp light.

Maybe it's the low tech end of it that I like.  I wouldn't think of writing without a computer for sake of making editions and corrections later, but when first getting my thoughts in some kind of solid form, I've prefered to go it the old fashioned way.  Things flow better somehow.  Maybe when I get settled into the room, I can have some desk space without the computer where I can just write or draw even by myself by that light.  Maybe it's something I've been missing...

It's times like this where I wish I were a coffee drinker.  

After being up late last night and having strange dreams about the Harry Potter boys, I was awake nearly with the sun today thanks to my Uncle Marvin.  He owns a siding and home construction business and came over around 8 to help Dad rip out some walls and and siding and put in new windows and a door in the front rooms.  They're still at it now.  I've been trying to help on and off all day, carrying away old foam boarding and siding pieces and brining in two-by-four deliveries after Mom makes Home Depot/Lowes runs.  Right now I'm taking care of lunch by watching the hot dogs and burgers on the stove.  

And boy am I sleepy... Why did I have to go and volunteer to close at work tonight?  I could take a nap after lunch without worrying about being late for my shift.  Oh well.  Guess I have to get in as much time as possible before vacation.  I put in for paid time off, but it won't account for very much.  Have to worry about not only spending money for Dave (not that he normally lets me spend on him while we're together, but still, just in case) but for this darn credit card issue.

Weather wise it hasn't been a bad day. It's been grey and rainy on and off.  We get a few moments of bright sun before the cloud cover rolls in.  But it's not cold, which is good.  Best to get this stuff out of the way now before any more serious thunder storms happen.  We're supposed to get them all week if I remember correctly. 

~*~*~*~

It feels really different trying to journal by computer as compared to a paper book.  I've always been better at writing out what I want to say before typing it, so typing straight is going to take some getting used to.  I've looked back at the "quality" of my entries the past few days and it hasn't really been there.  Then again, I'm not wirting my life story for commercial publication here.  I'm just jotting down what's on my mind at any giving time.  

At least this way both my hands and wrists get a work out.  When I write free hand, one hand takes the abuse.  I keep telling myself that one day I'll learn to do things like write and crochet with my left had so that I don't have one hand that's weak and another that's terribly cripple.  It's on my list with learning how to breath properly without damaging my system and getting into shape and learning to draw worth a darn.  Meaning that I might get there in a decade or two.  :S  

Though I also can't go and hide in the bathroom or the closet to be alone to write either.  

Well, we'll see.  I think only one person knows of this place anyway.

My visa bill from Target came in today.  I knew things would be bad, but I wasn't quite prepared.  Thanks to the ticket purchase, my card ballance is over $4000 and my minimums are up to $108. I was afraid to even look at the finance charges.  This is going to take much longer than I thought to pay all this off.  It's annoying that I have to keep paying back so much to these people, but I did get myself into it.  I don't have very much self control when it comes to spending, espeically if there's food involved.  I know there're many trips to the grocery store and the snack counter on past transations.  

That's part of the reason I got my debit card in the first place. If it's a situation where I need to pay in plastic, at leat I'll be taking from money I DO have rather than money I DON'T.  I've had it probably about six months now, and I'm glad I have it.  I've used it for PSO subscriptions (which I cancled yesterday seeing as I don't use my Cube account and I don't yet have the money to update to a paid Blue Burst account) and for putting gas in my tank when needed.  I still have issues with using it to buy snacks way too often. That's a habit I'll have to start curbing very soon.  Besides my body feeling like crap from giving in to Hostes apple pie cravings, I just can't afford it.  

Anyway, back to my credit delema.  Mom has suggested that it's time I find a card with a lower interest rate and do a ballance transfer.  It would seem like a logical thing to do, but I've seen my parents try to juggle such issues with more than one card, so it makes me a little nervous.  I only have one credit card, but it's also how I use my team member discount and how I act as importer to my UK friends.  I have my misgivings about getting rid of it right away.  As much as I loath it, I'll probably keep it around for the sake of the discount.  If my sister needs something from Target, I can use the card at the register and she can write a check to pay off that ballace so that it's taken care of that day.  I like to have it in case of such situations. I've been good about not using it though in general.  The tickets were the first time I used that card in a few months.  The trick has been to not carry it for the most part.  I used to take it to Toledo with me for gas and emergency purposes, but as I don't go up there anymore, that's no longer an issue.

Pretty much all my paycheque went to paying this month's bill and paying my parents for room and board.  It's not much, way less than I should really be paying them.  Still, from someone who brings home less than $400 every two weeks, it's a lot.  That new restaurant is going up quickly.  Maybe they'll still need staff .  Although there are way too many restaurants in that general area, beggers can't be choosers.

I think this system is going to take some getting used to...

I don't know how long I'll keep this.  I'm normally terrible at keeping journals.  I have more than one paper journal laying around that I kept for maybe a few months before getting either too lazy or too depressed to keep it going.  At least if I don't keep my live journal there's no paper waste.  I won't have another half empty book laying around being unused.  

I don't want to promise myself that I'll update it every day or every other day.  It'll be here mostly when I've got something on my mind that's bugging me (gives me a place to put quiz results too I guess).  Plus it's better to do such here than the Starwing board.  I don't want a majority of those people to know what goes on with me.  Besides, I have the tendency to accidentally start fights.  That's the last thing our community needs, and I especially don't want to jinx things now that we actually are beginning to make some kind of progress as far as reorganisation and updating is concerned.  

Now to figure out how to get those cute little fox emoticons to go with the mood settings...
